According to a report by Intel Market Research, the global NFC Mobile Payment Market was valued at USD 38.49 billion in 2025 and is projected to grow from USD 45.02 billion in 2026 to USD 159.71 billion by 2034, registering a CAGR of 16.9% during the forecast period. The market is witnessing rapid expansion as consumers increasingly adopt contactless payment solutions powered by Near Field Communication (NFC) technology. Rising smartphone penetration, widespread deployment of contactless payment terminals, expanding digital wallet ecosystems, and government initiatives promoting cashless economies are driving sustained market growth.
The growing adoption of NFC-enabled smartphones and digital wallets has significantly transformed the global payments landscape. Consumers increasingly prefer fast, secure, and convenient tap-to-pay transactions across retail stores, transportation systems, hospitality, and public services. Digital wallet platforms continue to integrate loyalty programs, biometric authentication, identity credentials, and transit passes, creating comprehensive payment ecosystems that enhance user convenience and accelerate market adoption.
